description:
&lt;p&gt;The Lister Pathology Blood Sciences department are looking for an enthusiastic experienced individual to work in the pathology services at East and North Hertfordshire Trust. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Duties will include receipting of samples, supporting the Biomedical Scientists in routine operation, maintenance of the various analysers across Biochemistry, Haematology and Blood Transfusion.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be required to work 37.5 hours per week flexibly, including shifts to cover the 24/7 service. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Come join our organisation and play a vital part in the growth and development of our service and in return, we will provide an environment that values its staff and offers excellent personal development and career opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal Secondments will also be considered.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kate Barrett, Blood Sciences Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address : katebarrett@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number : 01438284998&lt;/p&gt;
